def: Of or pertaining an acid intermediate between malic acid andmalamide, and known only by its salts.
Of or pertaining to a palinode, or retraction. J. Q. Adams.
The larva or grub of a large South American beetle (Calandrapalmarum), which lives in the pith of palm trees and sugar cane. Itis eaten by the natives, and esteemed a delicacy.
A kind of intercolumniation in an entablature, in which onlyone triglyph and two metopes are introduced.
